cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper involves machine learning models and their application in olfaction, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of electronic nose and smell sensors also suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The focus on training models to classify food and drink quality suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of unsupervised learning also suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of multiple models and their evaluation against baselines suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
